### Description

https://github.com/InternationalColorConsortium/iccDEV/issues/1230

from_json.hpp has type casting without checking/clamping ranges. Casting from float to int is the most dangerous of these, and triggers UBSan warnings when the float value is outside of the integer range.
```from_json.hpp:356:47: runtime error: 1.11111e+21 is outside the range of representable values of type 'int'```   
(original report appears to be header version 3.11.3 on Linux)

### Reproduction steps

https://github.com/InternationalColorConsortium/iccDEV/issues/1230

Any from_json code that converts from float to int can cause this.
Converting larger int to smaller ints can have the same problem.

### Expected vs. actual results
```from_json.hpp:356:47: runtime error: 1.11111e+21 is outside the range of representable values of type 'int'```
Expect no UBSan warnings from the json library code.

### Minimal code example
